cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with issues related to wireless ad hoc networks, specifically direct-sequence code-division multiple-access (DS-CDMA) networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves analysis of the outage probability in the presence of fading, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of guard zones and the exploration of tradeoffs between exclusion zones and CSMA guard zones may also relate to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves modeling and analysis of network geometry, which could fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
